01/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski met for seven hours Thursday (November 30th) with Italian Deputy National Anti-Mafia Prosecutor Francesco Mandoi. 
They discussed measures Macedonia should take to better fight corruption and organised crime, especially via legislative changes.
In other news Thursday, the Macedonian government decided to dispatch 35 soldiers and five commissioned officers to the international peacekeeping force in Iraq. 
The deployment begins this month. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 30/11/06)
